summary: Midoriya and Shinsou spend time on the same hero message boards/forums and have on occasion had very in-depth conversations with...
body:
Midoriya and Shinsou spend time on the same hero message boards/forums and have on occasion had very in-depth conversations with each other about their favorite heros. They don’t realize this until Midoriya starts making videos instead of just posts and Shinsou recognizes his voice. They have 100% RP’d with each other during middle school and are totally unsure how to feel about this.

They start playing BNHA version dungeons and dragons together with Tokoyami and a few 1B kids. Midoriya’s character is a blatant All Might ripoff. Shinsou’s is blatantly based on Aizawa.

summary: Who is your favorite hero from MHA so far?   Your favorite villain?  Best girl?  Best boy-o?  Fave quirk?
question: Who is your favorite hero from MHA so far?   Your favorite villain?  Best girl?  Best boy-o?  Fave quirk?
answer:
You really know how to ask questions, comrade. Seriously, it’s been nine days and I think I can formulate a coherent and reasonably response. Also, I’m only up to Season 2.

Favorite Hero: As much as I think Todoroki is awesome, I generally fall into the camp of I got to love the protagonist in order for the story to work. I might love other characters as much but it all starts with the protagonist. So, Deku is my favorite character. He works as a character people can insert themselves in but he isn’t blank. He’s really well-developed and you can feel the pain he feels when he’s just a quirk. And his determination when he’s quirkless to controlling his quirk to doing what is RIGHT versus what is JUST… yeah… Deku is my favorite hero. Right now, Todoroki, All Might, Tenya, and Ochaco all fall into that other category where I love them for different reasons and possibly equally to Deku but Deku gets the first spot. 

Favorite Villain: Bakugo or Mineta Shigaraki gives me the creeps & Kurogiri wins on the cool-look/villain with some sense of decorum even though he’s an evil bastard. Shigaraki cause, I tell you, dude is creepy and that works for me as a villain. Stain was kind of cool, but you could understand his motives.

Best girl: To be a cliche-addled mess… We’re going with Froppy. As much as I love Ochaco and Momo, there’s a uniqueness to Froppy that makes her the best girl. 

Best Boy-o: Okay, we’re going with Tenya because he’s got the honorable streak going and I’m always a sucker for characters that feel honor-bound to a cause or a person. 

Favorite Quirk: Christ, as much as I hate to admit this… Explosion. I mean, come on, like it doesn’t remind people of some other… possibly alchemy power… I just wish it was someone else’s…
